claim.claim-text:
11. A method of configuring a connection polarity for a network apparatus, comprising the steps of: 
enabling said network apparatus to operate in either a medium-dependent interface test mode or a medium-dependent interface crossover test mode; 
detecting a network signal within a first time period; 
if failing to detect a network signal within said first time period, selectively enabling said network apparatus to operate in either said medium-dependent interface test mode or said medium-dependent interface crossover test mode in accordance with a random number; and 
if a network signal is detected or a link is established within said first time period, enabling said network apparatus to stay at a stable state for at least a second time period; 
wherein if a network signal is continuously or a link is established, enabling said network apparatus to keep staying at said stable state.
